xmmsctrl: xmmsctrl (A small xmms control program)
xmmsctrl:
xmmsctrl: xmmsctrl is a small utility to control xmms from the command line.
xmmsctrl: Its goal is to be used coupled with sh to test xmms state and perform
xmmsctrl: an appropriate action, e.g. if playing then pause else play. The
xmmsctrl: interest of this is to bind keys in a window manager to have control
xmmsctrl: over xmms with keys that do play/next/pause, prev, control sound...
xmmsctrl:
xmmsctrl: http://user.it.uu.se/~adavid/utils/
xmmsctrl:
xmmsctrl: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
